    1. According to John Berger's "Ways of seeing", the majority of the worlds population percentage do not visit art museums. But of that priviledged population, which percentage of these countries have the highest attendance? a)GREECE b )POLAND c)HOLLAND
    2. My answer is... d for HOLLAND. Accoording to John Berger Holland is a very art conscience country with a very rich and vast amount of art history. If you would like to know more information about this subject you may browse http://phwww.cwis.uci.edu/cgi-bin/phww>Have fun

      Return to list of questions.

    3. Now with the answer to question number one answered, What is the correct percentage to answer number 1? a)5% b)20% c)35%
      My answer is...b)20% This answer gives insight into into the world of art and how much or how little the world of art is appreciated in other countries

      Return to list of questions.

    4. What is it called when a form of a sexual reproduction only involves on egg?
      My answer is... parthenogenis, It is the process of one egg being able to reproduce itself without engaging in the act of sexual intercourse. This process would be very useful if you and your partner were not on very good terms
    5. What is a chain of Amino Acids linked together, fold and coil in a specific chain sequence according to its genetic make-up?
      My answer is... "Protein". Your body is made of up of many proteins and proteins are the building blocks for everything. According to Professor Hoffman in the U.C.I biology department proteins are specifically designed for specific parts of the body in specific codes. If you would like more information please refer to http://phwww.cwis.uci.edu/cgi-bin/phwww
